WHERE THE REAL VALUE IS
===============================================================================

This framework has IMMEDIATE commercial value, just not through direct execution.

PATHWAY 1: IP LICENSING (RECOMMENDED)
  
  What You Sell: Complete MRV protocol + commercial framework + policy navigation
  
  Buyers: Carbon project developers who have capital but lack methodology
    • Climeworks (direct air capture, expanding to nature-based)
    • Charm Industrial (bio-oil sequestration, needs diversification)
    • Puro.earth (carbon removal marketplace, needs suppliers)
    • Indigo Ag (regenerative agriculture, carbon credits)
    • Microsoft Climate Innovation Fund (looking for novel CDR)
  
  Deal Structure:
    • 2-5% revenue share on carbon credits generated using your protocol
    • $50K-100K upfront licensing fee per territory/partner
    • Geographic exclusivity (e.g., "North America rights" vs. "EU rights")
    • Technical support retainer ($10K-20K/year for MRV guidance)
  
  Revenue Potential:
    • If partner deploys 10,000 hectares generating 35,000 tCO2/year
    • At $50/tCO2 = $1.75M annual carbon revenue
    • Your 3% = $52K/year passive income per partner
    • Goal: 5 partners across different regions = $260K/year royalties
  
  Timeline: 6-12 months to first deal
  Risk: 30-40% (buyers may not see value or have existing solutions)
  Capital Required: $25K-50K for pilot demonstration to prove concept

PATHWAY 2: POLICY CONSULTING (IMMEDIATE REVENUE)
  
  What You Sell: Climate policy expertise + CDR framework analysis
  
  Buyers:
    • NGOs (NRDC, The Nature Conservancy, Environmental Defense Fund)
    • Trade associations (Hemp Industries Association, Soil Health Institute)
    • State climate offices (California, New York, Washington)
    • Congressional committees (Agriculture, Energy & Commerce)
    • Philanthropic foundations (Bloomberg, Gates, Bezos Earth Fund)
  
  Services:
    • Policy analysis: "How should the 2024 Farm Bill support CDR?"
    • Testimony: Expert witness at congressional hearings
    • Grant writing: Help NGOs secure USDA/DOE funding for pilots
    • Technical review: Evaluate other CDR proposals for funders
  
  Revenue Potential:
    • Retainers: $5K-15K/month for ongoing advisory
    • Project-based: $25K-75K for policy brief development
    • Speaking fees: $5K-10K per congressional testimony
    • Goal: 2-3 retainers + 3-4 projects/year = $150K annual
  
  Timeline: 3-6 months to first contract
  Risk: 10-20% (your clinical ops + systems expertise is rare in climate policy)
  Capital Required: $0 (leverage existing expertise)

PATHWAY 3: DIRECT EXECUTION (NOT RECOMMENDED NOW)
  
  What You Do: Build the carbon removal company yourself
  
  Capital Required: $150M+ (initial 10,000 hectare deployment)
  Timeline: 7-10 years to break-even
  Risk: 50-65% chance of failure
  
  Why Not Now:
    • Post-layoff = you need revenue in 12-24 months, not 7-10 years
    • Capital-intensive = requires VC/PE investors who will dilute ownership
    • Operational complexity = requires agricultural expertise you don't have
    • Regulatory uncertainty = Farm Bill, 45Q implementation unclear
  
  When To Reconsider:
    • After securing $2M+ in licensing revenue (proves market demand)
    • When policy support clarifies (2025-2026 Farm Bill implementation)
    • If you find operational co-founder with hemp farming expertise
    • If impact investor offers patient capital (10+ year timeline)

